Criminal gangs, including drug cartels, are fighting for control over the “avocado business” in Mexico, since, according to some information, the profitability from the production and trade of avocados is comparable to the profit from the drug trade. For this reason, the epithet “blood diamond” is common in Europe in relation to avocados Mexico", a number of restaurants refuse to buy this fruit, excluding it from their menus, distancing themselves from the possible financing of Mexican organized crime[15][16]. .May be illegal in some jurisdictions under certain conditions.